nious production houses of the post-studio, post-war era; the collaborative approach of boutique animation and special-effect houses. Drawing on archival sources, this volume provides not only an overview of American animation history, but also, by focusing on the relationship between production and style, a unique approach to understanding animation in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAnimation (Cinematography)zUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aAnimation (Cinematography)zUnited StatesxHistoryy21st century. 0aAnimation (Cinematography). 7aPERFORMING ARTS / General.2bisacsh  aanimation, film, United States, television, independent, motion picture, web, cartoons, art, Disney, rubber hose, abstract, computer, puppet.1 aCurtis, Scott, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtis, Scott, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGadassik, Alla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGadassik, Alla.1 aJohnston, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnston, Andrew.1 aOhmer, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOhmer, Susan.1 aRehak, Bob, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRehak, Bob.1 aSandler, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSandler, Kevin.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts 2019z9783110605785oZDB-23-DPK08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2019 Englishz978311061001708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08